    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "literal": "This video introduces the concept of quaternions and their significance in describing 3D orientation. Quaternions provide a reliable and bug-free method for representing rotations in computer graphics, robotics, and virtual reality. They offer advantages over other methods, such as avoiding gimbal lock and providing seamless interpolation between orientations."
        }
